casebody.data:
Matthew FARR and Katie Farr, Respondents,
v.
Keith STROUD and Althea Stroud, Appellants. No. ED 106692 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, NORTHERN DIVISION. Filed: May 7, 2019
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied June 11, 2019
Application for Transfer Denied September 3, 2019 FOR APPELLANTS: Keith Stroud, Acting Pro Se, Althea Stroud, Acting Pro Se. FOR RESPONDENTS: Chelsea Hoffman, 105 East Lafayette St., Monticello, MO 63457. Before Lisa P. Page, C.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and Robert M. Clayton III, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Keith Stroud and Althea Stroud, acting pro se, appeal the judgment entered after a bench trial in favor of Matthew Farr and Katie Farr ("Landlords") as to Landlords' claim for unlawful detainer. We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision.

The judgment of the trial court is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
